{"word":"πυρσός","slug":"πυρσός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πυρσός</b></el> <el>(πυρσός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πῦρ'><el>πῦρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a firebrand, torch</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>fires</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>πυρσὸς ὕμνων</el> <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>the fires of love</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a beacon</i> or <i>signal-fire, bale-fire</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>πύρσα</el>, <i>watch-fires</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}